description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Volunteer Co-ordinator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary up to £25,000.00 per annum, dependant on experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week, to be worked in accordance with the needs of the service. This may include occasional weekends to support events&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you have a passion for volunteering?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to empower volunteers to deliver high quality support to patients, carers, families and employees at Mountbatten Isle of Wight?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking to make a significant social impact through your work?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for two talented Volunteer Co-ordinators who will be responsible for recruiting, training, supporting and developing our voluntary services across our community in the Isle of Wight, so that we can support our community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful candidate will have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good people skills, ability to put people first and ensure accessibility to the project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and listening skills, and the ability to manage challenging conversations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Motivation, organisation and excellent time management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience of working in a busy administrative role within a healthcare/charity organisation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we can Offer You &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a wide range of benefits to our employees including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free Onsite Parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development and Training opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous Annual Leave, Occupational Sickness and Maternity Benefit Schemes, subject to qualifying conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recognition of previous Agenda for Change NHS Continuous Service for incremental progression, annual leave, maternity and sickness benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pensions Schemes, including continuation of contributions to your NHS Pension scheme, subject to eligibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Local Benefit Scheme including discounts with all ferry operators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post is subject to an Enhanced DBS check the cost of which is covered by the Hospice.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion and visit about this opportunity, please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sally List, Head of Volunteer Development on 01983 217368&lt;/p&gt;
